<title>GREECE: OLYMPIC AIRWAYS PILOTS THREATENED WITH LAY-OFFS.</title>
<headline>OLYMPIC AIRWAYS PILOTS THREATENED WITH LAY-OFFS.</headline>
<dateline>ATHENS 1997-03-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Greece's Transport and Communications Minister Haralambos Kastanidis threatened to fire Olympic Airways pilots who have been on a strike since Monday, the Athens News Agency (ANA) said.</p>
<p>Greece is waiting for the outcome of a European Commission report on reforms at the national carrier.</p>
<p>&quot;No one will be allowed to abort the reform plan,&quot; Kastanidis was quoted as saying by the ANA.</p>
<p>He added that pilots who have caused problems for Olympic Airways will be suspended and brought before the Dismissal Council.</p>
<p>Pilots refuse to sign the new collective labour agreement. Instead, they are demanding a 12 percent salary increase. In 1996, they were awarded a total increase of 36 percent, said ANA.</p>
<p>Because of their strike two to three flights have been cancelled daily since Monday. --Margarita Sotiropoulou, Athens Newsroom +301 3311812-4</p>
